WEBVTT

00:04.613 --> 00:07.746
[ disquieting music ]

00:07.920 --> 00:10.706
♪

00:50.702 --> 00:53.444
[ footsteps ]

01:04.629 --> 01:07.110
[ The Association's
"Never My Love" playing ]

01:07.284 --> 01:10.113
♪

01:17.990 --> 01:22.517
SINGER:
♪ You asked me
if there'll come a time ♪

01:22.691 --> 01:25.824
♪ When I grow tired of you ♪

01:25.998 --> 01:27.957
♪

01:28.131 --> 01:30.177
♪ Never, my love ♪

01:30.351 --> 01:33.093
♪

01:33.267 --> 01:35.051
♪ Never, my love ♪

01:35.225 --> 01:38.402
♪

01:38.576 --> 01:42.711
♪ You wonder
if this heart of mine ♪

01:42.885 --> 01:47.237
♪ Will lose its desire
for you ♪

01:47.324 --> 01:50.022
♪ Never, my love ♪

01:50.197 --> 01:53.156
♪

01:53.330 --> 01:55.550
♪ Never, my love ♪

01:55.724 --> 01:58.596
♪

01:58.770 --> 02:02.470
♪ What makes you think
love will end ♪

02:02.644 --> 02:05.255
♪ When you know that
my whole life depends... ♪

02:05.386 --> 02:07.301
[ groans ]

02:07.431 --> 02:09.607
[ wheezing ]

02:09.694 --> 02:11.305
ARVIN:
I say we kill her,

02:11.435 --> 02:13.176
leave her for the beasts.

02:13.307 --> 02:14.525
You know Fraser's got
his hands full for a while.

02:16.397 --> 02:17.615
The still...

02:17.746 --> 02:20.140
- [ whimpers ]
- [ explosion ]

02:20.227 --> 02:21.880
CLAIRE: Well that was you.

02:21.967 --> 02:24.535
Well, aren't you
the clever one...

02:24.622 --> 02:26.146
Dr. Rawlings?

02:28.539 --> 02:30.237
You never thought
anyone'd find out

02:30.367 --> 02:33.153
about your little
newspaper column, did you?

02:33.240 --> 02:35.155
Well, now you're gonna repent
for your sin.

02:35.242 --> 02:38.375
I was just trying to help.

02:38.506 --> 02:41.596
Spreading dangerous ideas,
what you mean...

02:41.726 --> 02:44.294
telling women
how to deceive their husbands,

02:44.425 --> 02:46.775
how to deny them
their God-given rights,

02:46.905 --> 02:49.169
telling my wife
to avoid my bed.

02:50.909 --> 02:53.782
And I'm gonna take you
to Brownsville,

02:53.869 --> 02:56.959
and you're gonna confess
to the womenfolk there,

02:57.046 --> 03:00.441
and they're gonna see you
for the charlatan that you are.

03:00.571 --> 03:02.573
[ groans ]

03:02.704 --> 03:05.359
[ "Never My Love" playing ]

03:05.533 --> 03:08.318
♪

03:08.449 --> 03:10.015
[ doorbell rings ]

03:10.190 --> 03:12.583
♪

03:12.714 --> 03:15.107
[ laughing ]

03:15.282 --> 03:17.414
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love... ♪

03:17.545 --> 03:18.502
Happy Thanksgiving, Uncle.

03:22.680 --> 03:23.899
[ yelps ]

03:25.640 --> 03:28.338
[ cries out ]

03:28.469 --> 03:29.861
You fucking bastard!

03:29.992 --> 03:32.255
[ whimpers ] You're going to go
to hell for this.

03:32.386 --> 03:34.214
It's a curse!

03:34.344 --> 03:36.259
Hodge, you've done it now.

03:36.390 --> 03:38.827
Don't touch that woman
and don't draw her blood.

03:38.957 --> 03:41.133
We did hear talk of her.
She's a conjure woman.

03:42.657 --> 03:43.788
CLAIRE:
That's right.

03:43.919 --> 03:46.748
You touch me again,

03:46.835 --> 03:49.490
and you'll all be dead by dawn!

03:49.620 --> 03:50.708
I said don't do it!

03:50.795 --> 03:52.449
She will kill us all!

03:52.580 --> 03:53.624
LIONEL:
That's enough, both of you.

03:53.711 --> 03:55.235
Just tie her up over there.

03:58.586 --> 04:00.457
WENDIGO:
So where do you come from?

04:00.588 --> 04:02.067
CLAIRE:
You know where I come from.

04:02.198 --> 04:03.895
You bloody kidnapped me.

04:04.026 --> 04:07.029
Where did you come from
before you settled here?

04:10.032 --> 04:13.427
Do you have clear night skies
where you come from?

04:13.557 --> 04:16.691
I can't tell one star
from another
like some people can.

04:16.821 --> 04:20.303
The Moon--that's the same
wherever you go.

04:21.957 --> 04:26.440
Looks like a man on the moon...

04:26.570 --> 04:28.268
staring back at us.

04:30.879 --> 04:33.751
[ indistinct chatter,
laughter ]

04:33.882 --> 04:35.405
MAN:
Well, her legs aren't tied.

04:35.536 --> 04:37.364
[ laughter ]

04:37.494 --> 04:38.539
[ "Never My Love" playing ]

04:38.713 --> 04:40.105
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love ♪

04:40.280 --> 04:43.457
♪

04:43.631 --> 04:46.590
♪ Never, my love ♪

04:46.677 --> 04:48.940
♪

04:49.114 --> 04:51.552
♪ What makes you think
love will end... ♪

04:51.682 --> 04:54.729
You're shaking so hard,
it's making my teeth rattle.

04:54.903 --> 04:59.081
SINGER:
♪ That depends ♪

04:59.255 --> 05:02.389
♪ On you... ♪

05:02.476 --> 05:03.303
TEBBE: You hungry?

05:04.695 --> 05:06.393
Go on.

05:10.919 --> 05:12.964
My name is Tebbe.

05:13.095 --> 05:16.403
You remember that. Remember me was good to you.

05:16.490 --> 05:18.709
You tell your spirits
they don't hurt Tebbe.

05:18.796 --> 05:20.058
He tried to help you.

05:24.933 --> 05:26.195
Thank you, Tebbe.

05:30.634 --> 05:34.464
Tebbe, how much longer
before we reach Brownsville?

05:34.595 --> 05:36.814
TEBBE: Two days after we cross the creek.

05:36.945 --> 05:39.208
[ breathes deeply ]

05:44.518 --> 05:46.650
We will swim the horses across.

05:46.737 --> 05:47.869
You will come with me.

05:47.999 --> 05:49.436
You shouldn't go with them.

05:49.566 --> 05:51.263
Lionel Brown, Hodgepile--
they're all going to die...

05:51.394 --> 05:53.004
and everyone with them.

05:53.135 --> 05:55.659
You've heard
of the water horses,
the kelpies?

05:55.790 --> 05:59.663
They take you down, drown you,
and eat you.

05:59.794 --> 06:03.493
Yes, yes, but the water horse
is my friend,

06:03.624 --> 06:05.060
and if-if you just--

06:05.190 --> 06:07.454
w-when we're across the creek,
you-you let me go.

06:07.584 --> 06:09.630
It'll rise up
and carry me away.

06:09.760 --> 06:12.546
Just-just let go of me
in the water,

06:12.633 --> 06:13.764
and I swear it won't cause you
any harm.

06:18.508 --> 06:20.467
Thank you.

06:20.554 --> 06:21.685
- ARVIN: I'll take her across.
- No, no!

06:21.772 --> 06:22.686
I'm going with him!

06:22.817 --> 06:24.601
No!

06:24.688 --> 06:27.474
[ "Never My Love" playing ]

06:27.604 --> 06:30.520
[ indistinct chatter,
laughter ]

06:30.694 --> 06:33.480
♪

06:33.654 --> 06:35.395
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love ♪

06:35.569 --> 06:37.440
♪ Never, my love... ♪

06:37.571 --> 06:38.485
- No!
- I said no!

06:38.615 --> 06:41.357
Jesus H. Roosevelt Christ!

06:41.444 --> 06:42.402
LIONEL:
You halfwits!

06:44.621 --> 06:46.667
She's cursed you again, Uncle.
She'll curse us all.

06:46.797 --> 06:48.190
LIONEL:
That's enough, Cuddy.

06:48.320 --> 06:50.366
[ groans ]

06:50.497 --> 06:52.412
Not one more word
out of you.

06:52.542 --> 06:55.937
Not to them, not to me.

06:56.067 --> 06:58.113
Not one more damn word.

06:58.243 --> 07:00.855
[ "Never My Love" playing ]

07:00.942 --> 07:03.640
♪

07:03.727 --> 07:06.687
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love ♪

07:06.861 --> 07:08.471
♪ Never, my love... ♪

07:08.602 --> 07:11.431
[ laughter ]

07:16.914 --> 07:18.350
Don't you stare at me.

07:20.178 --> 07:21.745
I'll put you somewhere
you can't stare!

07:21.876 --> 07:23.138
[ groans ]

07:23.268 --> 07:24.748
LIONEL:
On your feet, bitch.

07:24.879 --> 07:27.708
[ grunting ]

07:27.838 --> 07:30.754
I'm gonna put
some manners on you.

07:30.885 --> 07:35.237
- [ muffled screaming ]
- Yeah, yeah.

07:35.324 --> 07:36.673
[ muffled sobs ]

07:36.847 --> 07:37.979
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love... ♪

07:38.109 --> 07:39.981
JAMIE:
But James is far better.

07:40.111 --> 07:42.679
YOUNG IAN:
No, no, no, no, no.
It's got to be Ian.

07:42.810 --> 07:45.595
Oh, we're thinking
of something a bit more hip,
like Ringo.

07:45.726 --> 07:47.423
- Like Ringo.
- Everyone.

07:47.510 --> 07:48.859
JOCASTA:
What if it's a wee girl?

07:48.990 --> 07:50.557
Jocasta's a lovely name.
We'll call her Jo.

07:50.731 --> 07:53.647
♪

07:53.734 --> 07:56.084
[ laughter ]

07:56.258 --> 07:58.303
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love ♪

07:58.478 --> 08:00.654
♪ Never, my love ♪

08:00.828 --> 08:02.264
♪ Never, my love ♪♪♪

08:02.438 --> 08:04.832
♪

08:04.962 --> 08:07.748
[ wheezing ]

08:07.922 --> 08:10.707
♪

08:15.233 --> 08:17.888
[ coughing, wheezes ]

08:28.464 --> 08:31.119
[ gasping ]

08:31.249 --> 08:33.295
Does the name Ringo Starr
mean anything to you?

08:37.081 --> 08:38.735
What?

08:38.866 --> 08:40.389
Does the name Ringo Starr
mean anything to you?

08:41.869 --> 08:44.654
[ dramatic music ]

08:44.828 --> 08:47.875
♪

08:47.962 --> 08:51.574
[ gasps ]
H-he's a drummer.

08:51.705 --> 08:52.836
I knew you had to be.
I knew it. I knew it.

08:54.272 --> 08:55.752
I knew that advice
from Dr. Rawlings

08:55.883 --> 08:58.102
didn't come from anybody
in this time.

08:58.233 --> 09:00.017
I just never thought I'd find
another one, not ever.

09:00.148 --> 09:02.280
Please, untie me.

09:02.411 --> 09:04.152
I can't.

09:04.239 --> 09:05.588
You know what they're planning.

09:05.719 --> 09:07.329
It's mostly just talk.

09:07.459 --> 09:09.592
[ sobs ]

09:09.679 --> 09:11.681
They think you're a witch.
They're scared to death of you.

09:11.812 --> 09:12.900
- I know you're not.
- [ distant laughter ]

09:13.030 --> 09:14.858
Who are you?

09:14.989 --> 09:15.990
CLAIRE:
You know who I am.

09:16.120 --> 09:17.469
Who are you?

09:17.600 --> 09:19.602
My name's Wendigo Donner.

09:19.689 --> 09:23.345
I traveled back with a group
of American Indians from 1968.

09:23.475 --> 09:25.521
Otter Tooth.

09:25.652 --> 09:27.610
Robert Springer.

09:27.741 --> 09:29.003
You know Bob?

09:29.133 --> 09:30.831
Where is he?

09:30.918 --> 09:31.962
He's dead.

09:32.136 --> 09:34.399
♪

09:34.530 --> 09:35.531
How?

09:35.662 --> 09:38.012
The Mohawk.

09:38.099 --> 09:39.927
- They killed him.
- That doesn't make sense.

09:40.057 --> 09:41.015
- We came back to save them.
- Come on.

09:41.145 --> 09:42.451
I'll tell you
everything I know.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.148
Just, please...

09:44.235 --> 09:45.672
cut me loose.

09:45.802 --> 09:47.151
Get two horses,
and let's go.

09:47.282 --> 09:50.241
Lionel, he'll--
he's crazy.

09:50.328 --> 09:52.113
He'll kill me.
He'll kill both of us.

09:52.243 --> 09:55.464
Okay?
I need to get home.

09:55.595 --> 09:58.206
I've been trying
for too long.

09:58.336 --> 10:00.556
I need gemstones.

10:00.687 --> 10:02.036
I have gemstones.

10:02.166 --> 10:03.864
I know where a stone circle is.

10:03.994 --> 10:06.997
You cut me loose,
I'll get you home.

10:07.128 --> 10:08.477
Forget the horses.
Let's go now.

10:08.608 --> 10:10.522
Okay.
We need to wait.

10:10.610 --> 10:12.655
- We need to wait
until they fall asleep.
- LIONEL: Donner!

10:12.786 --> 10:14.352
What the hell you doing
down there?

10:14.483 --> 10:15.832
Just making sure
she's tied tight!

10:15.963 --> 10:18.748
Please, let's go.

10:18.879 --> 10:20.663
- I should've known
what you were...
- [ laughter ]

10:20.750 --> 10:22.143
Before Dr. Rawlings...

10:22.534 --> 10:24.580
Jesus H. Roosevelt Christ.

10:24.667 --> 10:27.017
You don't act afraid of men.

10:27.148 --> 10:29.498
Most of the women from now do.

10:29.629 --> 10:31.500
You ought to act more afraid.

10:31.587 --> 10:33.807
No, no.
[ moaning ]

10:36.897 --> 10:39.639
[ coughs, wheezing ]

10:41.989 --> 10:44.034
SINGER:
♪ With me ♪

10:44.121 --> 10:47.908
♪ With me ♪

10:48.038 --> 10:49.910
- ♪ With me... ♪
- [ thunder rumbles ]

10:50.040 --> 10:52.086
Promised Cuddy here
a little bit of fun.

10:52.216 --> 10:53.609
- All right, Cuddy.
- He did.

10:53.740 --> 10:55.219
LIONEL:
Now listen up.

10:55.350 --> 10:57.918
Shoot twixt the wind
and the water.

10:58.048 --> 10:59.136
[ muffled screaming ]

10:59.267 --> 11:00.703
Shh.

11:00.834 --> 11:03.227
Don't fight me.
Now, now--

11:03.358 --> 11:04.925
- Now, don't fight.
Hey, hey, d--
- [ blow lands ]

11:05.055 --> 11:06.143
[ muffled screaming ]

11:06.274 --> 11:09.059
Hey, hush, hush.

11:09.233 --> 11:11.975
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love ♪

11:12.149 --> 11:14.935
♪

11:15.065 --> 11:15.849
CUDDY: Don't!

11:17.459 --> 11:20.505
Hush now.
Hush now. Hush now.

11:20.636 --> 11:23.508
[ groaning ]

11:26.990 --> 11:29.863
[ Lionel laughing ]

11:29.993 --> 11:32.300
What, are you finished
already?

11:32.430 --> 11:34.998
You are one sorry lobcock.

11:35.129 --> 11:37.044
[ laughing ]

11:39.699 --> 11:41.657
Oh, dear me, Cuddy.

11:41.788 --> 11:43.615
[ chuckles ]

11:43.746 --> 11:46.183
I apologize about my nephew.

11:46.314 --> 11:49.752
He's just a boy. What does he know?

11:49.883 --> 11:53.451
But you, you being pretending
to be a man...

11:58.065 --> 12:01.155
[ Claire whimpering ]

12:01.285 --> 12:02.896
[ blow lands,
Claire cries out ]

12:05.855 --> 12:08.902
[ Lionel grunting ]

12:14.864 --> 12:15.691
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love... ♪

12:15.822 --> 12:18.085
Table looks ready.

12:18.215 --> 12:20.391
Checked on the turkey.

12:20.522 --> 12:25.048
Oh, it gets bigger every year,
as does our family.

12:25.135 --> 12:28.443
SINGER:
♪ What makes you think
love will end ♪

12:28.617 --> 12:33.404
♪ When you know that
my whole life depends... ♪

12:33.535 --> 12:36.277
Are my cousin
and the professor here yet?

12:36.364 --> 12:38.758
Oh, they're on their way--
delayed in the holiday rush.

12:38.888 --> 12:41.456
First, I, uh...

12:41.586 --> 12:43.980
I want to thank you all for being here today.

12:44.111 --> 12:47.244
I'm grateful
for my beautiful wife,

12:47.375 --> 12:49.769
blood of my blood, bone of my bone.

12:49.856 --> 12:52.641
♪

12:52.772 --> 12:55.296
My heart was yours

12:55.426 --> 12:58.342
since I first saw ye.

12:58.429 --> 13:01.911
Ye've held my soul
in your two hands,

13:02.042 --> 13:04.566
kept it safe.

13:04.653 --> 13:06.655
Slàinte.

13:06.742 --> 13:09.223
♪

13:09.353 --> 13:12.008
[ Lionel grunts, panting ]

13:22.018 --> 13:23.715
Not so high and mighty now, are we?

13:23.846 --> 13:25.805
[ pants ]

13:25.892 --> 13:27.807
Mm.

13:30.548 --> 13:32.724
Who's next for a go
with the hedge whore?

13:32.812 --> 13:35.640
[ laughter ]

13:45.781 --> 13:46.695
♪

13:46.826 --> 13:49.089
[ laughter ]

13:49.219 --> 13:51.308
[ speaking indistinctly ]

13:51.439 --> 13:52.875
Another wee Fraser
on the way.

13:53.006 --> 13:54.442
[ gasps ]
Hi!

13:54.529 --> 13:56.748
Happy Thanksgiving, Auntie.

13:56.879 --> 13:59.839
I'm gonna make
some extra plates

13:59.969 --> 14:02.102
with some more extra
sweet potato for Jemmy.

14:02.276 --> 14:04.408
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love... ♪

14:04.539 --> 14:06.149
JAMIE:
Dinna fash.

14:06.236 --> 14:07.150
I'm sure Roger and Bree'll
be here soon.

14:07.237 --> 14:08.848
♪

14:09.022 --> 14:10.762
SINGER:
♪ My love ♪

14:10.937 --> 14:12.852
♪

14:12.982 --> 14:16.159
[ doorbell rings,
chatter and laughter ]

14:16.290 --> 14:17.726
YOUNG IAN:
Roger and Bree are here.

14:17.857 --> 14:18.988
MARSALI:
Finally!

14:19.162 --> 14:21.469
♪

14:21.643 --> 14:24.037
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love ♪

14:24.211 --> 14:26.256
♪ Never, my love ♪

14:26.430 --> 14:28.650
♪ Never, my love ♪

14:28.824 --> 14:30.304
♪ My love... ♪

14:30.391 --> 14:32.175
Mrs. Fraser?

14:32.306 --> 14:34.525
Yes.

14:34.612 --> 14:38.051
We're sorry to have to tell you
this at Thanksgiving, but...

14:38.138 --> 14:40.140
Mr. and Mrs. MacKenzie
were killed in a car accident

14:40.270 --> 14:41.706
with their child.

14:41.837 --> 14:44.231
[ dramatic music ]

14:44.318 --> 14:46.146
Oh.

14:46.276 --> 14:48.409
The conditions on the highway
were extremely treacherous.

14:48.496 --> 14:50.802
♪

14:50.933 --> 14:53.283
A truck lost its brakes.

14:53.414 --> 14:54.328
There was a collision involving Mr. MacKenzie's vehicle.

14:54.458 --> 14:56.069
No...

14:56.199 --> 14:57.287
OFFICER:
Paramedics arrived and worked

14:57.418 --> 14:59.202
to save him and his family,

14:59.333 --> 15:02.205
but, unfortunately,
their injuries were fatal.

15:02.292 --> 15:03.424
No...

15:03.511 --> 15:04.642
♪

15:07.994 --> 15:10.779
[ wind gusting ]

15:19.048 --> 15:21.181
[ dramatic music ]

15:21.268 --> 15:22.312
- I woke up!
- [ Brianna coughs ]

15:22.486 --> 15:23.705
♪

15:23.835 --> 15:25.315
Mom, Da?

15:25.446 --> 15:28.318
Are ye all right?

15:28.405 --> 15:30.146
I just feel like I've been
turned inside out.

15:30.233 --> 15:32.148
♪

15:32.279 --> 15:33.976
BRIANNA:
We made it.

15:34.107 --> 15:36.065
Aye.
[ exhales deeply ]

15:36.196 --> 15:37.066
JEMMY:
Look.

15:37.240 --> 15:40.287
♪

15:40.417 --> 15:43.072
[ both breathing heavily ]

15:43.246 --> 15:45.988
♪

15:51.254 --> 15:52.864
What the devil?

15:52.952 --> 15:55.041
Ye're back.

15:55.215 --> 15:56.956
♪

15:57.086 --> 15:58.392
How?

15:58.566 --> 16:01.438
♪

16:01.569 --> 16:04.224
I-I don't know.

16:04.354 --> 16:06.095
I was thinking about home.

16:06.226 --> 16:08.228
So was I.

16:08.402 --> 16:11.144
♪

16:14.364 --> 16:17.280
[ upbeat music ]

16:17.367 --> 16:20.153
♪

16:46.657 --> 16:49.617
We can make camp here,
or we can forge ahead.

16:49.704 --> 16:52.272
Oh, let's make camp
and rest.

16:52.402 --> 16:54.143
We can surprise them tomorrow.

16:58.756 --> 17:00.236
Roger, will you grab Jem?

17:03.283 --> 17:06.155
[ dramatic music ]

17:06.286 --> 17:07.765
Da lit the cross.

17:07.896 --> 17:09.985
Oh, God.

17:10.159 --> 17:13.249
♪

17:13.380 --> 17:15.295
Aye. He said he wouldn't light
it again unless...

17:15.469 --> 17:16.992
♪

17:17.123 --> 17:17.993
Let's go.

17:18.167 --> 17:20.952
♪

17:30.223 --> 17:32.921
I've packed some salted meats
for you and the men, sir.

17:33.052 --> 17:34.836
Thank you, Lizzie.

17:34.923 --> 17:37.752
♪

17:47.762 --> 17:49.546
Bree.

17:49.677 --> 17:50.678
Roger.

17:50.765 --> 17:51.766
What happened?

17:53.855 --> 17:56.205
It--it didn't work.
What is going on?

17:56.336 --> 17:59.121
On the way back,
we saw the cross.

17:59.252 --> 18:00.905
There's been an attack
on the ridge.

18:01.036 --> 18:01.950
They've taken your mother.

18:02.037 --> 18:04.126
♪

18:04.257 --> 18:05.997
I think it was the Browns.

18:06.128 --> 18:07.564
We're gonna get her back.

18:07.695 --> 18:09.000
- I'm coming with you.
- JAMIE: No.

18:09.131 --> 18:10.306
Brianna, it's too dangerous.

18:10.437 --> 18:11.655
- BRIANNA: Dad--
- You'll stay here

18:11.742 --> 18:13.570
with the rest of the men,
guard the ridge.

18:13.701 --> 18:15.224
JOSIAH:
I'd want to come.

18:15.355 --> 18:17.183
I'm a fine shot.

18:17.313 --> 18:19.010
Ye said so yerself.

18:19.098 --> 18:19.968
It's not war.

18:21.404 --> 18:22.623
It's for Mistress Claire.

18:22.753 --> 18:23.798
Then I'm coming, too.

18:25.669 --> 18:27.715
You called me

18:27.845 --> 18:30.326
at the gathering,
at the fire.

18:30.457 --> 18:32.633
Stand by my side,
son of my house.

18:32.720 --> 18:34.983
Did you mean that?

18:35.114 --> 18:36.158
Ye ken I did.

18:36.245 --> 18:38.595
Well, I meant it, too.

18:38.726 --> 18:40.293
There are times
for men of peace

18:40.423 --> 18:41.990
and a time for men of blood.

18:42.077 --> 18:43.905
♪

18:44.035 --> 18:45.211
I will stand by you.

18:45.385 --> 18:48.127
♪

19:00.530 --> 19:02.271
[ horse neighs ]

19:02.445 --> 19:05.187
♪

19:13.282 --> 19:15.241
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love ♪

19:15.415 --> 19:18.026
♪

19:18.200 --> 19:20.420
♪ Never, my love ♪

19:20.594 --> 19:23.684
♪

19:23.858 --> 19:27.775
♪ You say you fear
I'll change my mind ♪

19:27.949 --> 19:31.300
♪ That I won't require you ♪

19:31.474 --> 19:33.172
♪

19:33.346 --> 19:35.391
♪ Never, my love ♪

19:35.565 --> 19:38.873
♪ Never, my love ♪

19:38.960 --> 19:41.441
- ♪ Never, my love ♪
- ♪ Never, my love ♪

19:41.615 --> 19:43.530
♪

19:43.704 --> 19:46.576
♪ How can you think
love will end ♪

19:46.750 --> 19:47.708
♪ When I've asked you... ♪

19:47.838 --> 19:49.013
[ screaming ]

19:49.144 --> 19:50.145
JAMIE: Claire!

19:50.319 --> 19:53.453
♪

19:53.583 --> 19:55.629
- [ man screams ]
- JAMIE: Claire!

19:55.803 --> 19:58.632
♪

20:00.286 --> 20:01.635
Claire!

20:11.906 --> 20:12.994
JAMIE:
Claire!

20:25.180 --> 20:27.182
[ groans ]

20:27.313 --> 20:29.402
[ horse neighs ]

20:29.532 --> 20:30.664
JAMIE:
Claire!

20:30.751 --> 20:32.405
- [ men grunting ]
- Claire!

20:40.978 --> 20:43.633
[ "Never My Love" playing ]

20:43.807 --> 20:46.593
♪

20:50.988 --> 20:53.556
SINGER:
♪ Never, my love... ♪

20:53.643 --> 20:57.343
Dinna be afraid.

20:57.473 --> 20:59.519
Just the two of us now.

20:59.693 --> 21:02.652
♪

21:02.783 --> 21:03.479
JAMIE:
Claire!

21:06.613 --> 21:08.354
- Claire!
- [ moaning softly ]

21:08.441 --> 21:11.095
[ men yelling ]

21:11.226 --> 21:13.663
[ whimpers ]

21:13.794 --> 21:17.450
[ breathing heavily ]

21:17.580 --> 21:20.540
[ whimpering ]

21:20.670 --> 21:23.412
[ melancholy music ]

21:23.586 --> 21:26.328
♪

21:35.903 --> 21:39.254
[ sobs softly ]

21:39.428 --> 21:41.735
♪

21:43.737 --> 21:46.957
You are alive.

21:47.088 --> 21:49.395
You are whole,
mo nighean donn?

21:49.569 --> 21:52.311
♪

22:05.802 --> 22:07.587
There are some left
still alive.

22:10.241 --> 22:12.461
[ Claire whimpers ]

22:12.635 --> 22:15.421
♪

22:15.508 --> 22:18.119
Will you have your vengeance
upon them, Mistress?

22:18.249 --> 22:19.599
[ whimpers ]

22:19.729 --> 22:22.515
She's bound by an oath.

22:22.645 --> 22:23.907
She may not kill,

22:24.038 --> 22:26.823
for her own life.

22:26.910 --> 22:28.477
It is myself that kills
for her.

22:28.608 --> 22:30.436
And I.

22:30.610 --> 22:33.482
♪

22:33.613 --> 22:34.788
And I, milady.

22:34.962 --> 22:37.791
♪

22:43.971 --> 22:45.799
Who?

22:45.929 --> 22:47.453
How many?

22:47.627 --> 22:50.369
♪

22:52.458 --> 22:55.156
I don't know.

22:55.243 --> 22:58.072
♪

23:03.991 --> 23:06.210
Kill them all.

23:06.297 --> 23:09.126
[ dark music ]

23:09.300 --> 23:12.086
♪

23:16.438 --> 23:19.354
[ men groaning ]

23:19.528 --> 23:22.401
♪

23:28.276 --> 23:30.496
[ gunshot ]

23:30.626 --> 23:33.194
[ blades plunging,
men screaming ]

23:33.368 --> 23:36.415
♪

23:36.545 --> 23:39.200
[ gunshots, men screaming ]

23:39.374 --> 23:42.159
♪

23:45.511 --> 23:46.468
It is done.

23:46.555 --> 23:49.428
♪

23:52.909 --> 23:55.695
[ gentle music ]

23:55.869 --> 23:58.654
♪

24:54.797 --> 24:56.625
You see that they are dead.

24:56.799 --> 24:59.585
♪

25:11.248 --> 25:14.730
MYERS:
Jamie, this one's alive.

25:14.861 --> 25:17.428
[ cocks gun ]

25:17.559 --> 25:20.519
Wait!
Don't kill him yet.

25:20.649 --> 25:22.303
It's Lionel.

25:22.433 --> 25:24.958
[ dark music ]

25:25.132 --> 25:27.961
♪

25:29.528 --> 25:31.617
There are questions.

25:31.747 --> 25:34.271
Aye.

25:34.402 --> 25:36.360
Ask them now,
or take him with us?

25:36.447 --> 25:37.710
♪

25:37.840 --> 25:39.276
[ groans ]

25:39.450 --> 25:42.236
♪

25:44.499 --> 25:46.457
I want to take Claire home.

25:46.632 --> 25:49.417
♪

25:50.984 --> 25:52.855
We'll go on ahead.

25:52.986 --> 25:54.901
You and Myers bring him with you.

25:55.031 --> 25:56.598
MYERS:
Aye.

25:56.685 --> 25:59.514
[ dramatic music ]

25:59.601 --> 26:02.430
♪

26:34.636 --> 26:35.811
Marsali?

26:37.900 --> 26:40.599
She's alive, Sassenach.

26:43.689 --> 26:44.646
She and the baby.

26:47.040 --> 26:48.824
Felt it kicking strong
in her belly.

26:55.526 --> 26:56.615
Geordie's dead.

27:06.189 --> 27:09.715
Was there an Indian there?

27:12.543 --> 27:14.937
No.

27:15.068 --> 27:17.026
Why do you ask?

27:17.157 --> 27:18.985
He was like me...

27:21.727 --> 27:23.511
From the future.

27:25.861 --> 27:26.993
Did he harm you?

27:34.087 --> 27:35.654
He didn't help me.

27:37.264 --> 27:38.700
He's gone now...

27:40.789 --> 27:42.095
Whoever he was.

27:46.665 --> 27:48.405
I thought I saw Roger.

27:51.408 --> 27:53.410
My mind is playing tricks
on me.

27:53.541 --> 27:54.585
No.

27:56.979 --> 27:58.589
Ye didna imagine it.

27:58.720 --> 28:03.551
Roger, Bree, Jemmy...

28:03.638 --> 28:05.640
[ tender music ]

28:05.771 --> 28:06.815
They've come home.

28:06.989 --> 28:09.818
♪

28:23.876 --> 28:27.140
[ wagon wheels rattling ]

28:27.314 --> 28:30.752
♪

28:30.839 --> 28:33.189
[ footsteps departing,
descending stairs ]

28:33.276 --> 28:36.105
♪

29:02.001 --> 29:03.698
I thought
I'd never see you again.

29:03.829 --> 29:06.309
Shh.
Mom...

29:06.440 --> 29:08.877
I'm home.

29:09.051 --> 29:11.837
♪

29:23.065 --> 29:24.719
[ exhales deeply ]

29:24.893 --> 29:27.722
♪

29:48.961 --> 29:51.964
[ brush scraping ]

29:58.187 --> 30:00.537
[ breathes shakily ]

30:27.390 --> 30:30.785
You have my hand, Mama,
and my ear,

30:30.916 --> 30:32.656
if you need it.

30:36.486 --> 30:38.184
[ door closes ]

30:42.057 --> 30:44.755
[ breathes deeply ]

31:03.949 --> 31:06.299
[ footsteps approach,
door opens ]

31:09.606 --> 31:11.913
[ door closes ]

31:15.090 --> 31:18.224
The sight of you
tears my heart...

31:18.354 --> 31:19.355
fills me full of rage.

31:19.486 --> 31:21.314
I feel...

31:21.444 --> 31:23.142
I feel I must kill someone.

31:25.274 --> 31:26.232
Lionel.

31:28.799 --> 31:30.236
Is he still...

31:30.366 --> 31:31.890
In the surgery, tied up.

31:33.587 --> 31:36.416
The men gave him
quite a beating.

31:36.546 --> 31:38.853
I'll ask questions
and have answers...

31:38.984 --> 31:41.725
find out
what they were planning.

31:41.856 --> 31:43.031
Will you let him live?

31:47.688 --> 31:49.690
Is your oath so strong, then?

31:49.820 --> 31:52.649
[ mournful music ]

31:52.823 --> 31:54.477
♪

31:54.608 --> 31:56.697
I'm glad the others are dead.

31:56.871 --> 31:59.700
♪

32:00.875 --> 32:02.790
I'm sorry that I am.

32:02.877 --> 32:05.793
♪

32:14.671 --> 32:17.109
I don't want you to worry
about me.

32:17.239 --> 32:19.024
Ah, I'm just a little shaken.

32:19.154 --> 32:20.721
Claire, I ken
what it feels like--

32:20.808 --> 32:23.158
No.

32:23.289 --> 32:25.552
No, I have lived

32:25.639 --> 32:29.077
through a fucking world war...

32:29.164 --> 32:32.863
and I have lost a child.

32:33.038 --> 32:35.127
♪

32:35.257 --> 32:36.606
I lost two husbands.

32:36.693 --> 32:39.218
I've been starved
with an army,

32:39.348 --> 32:40.828
and I-I've been beaten,
and I've been betrayed,

32:40.959 --> 32:44.136
and I've--
[ sobs ] I've...

32:44.266 --> 32:46.747
I've been imprisoned,
and I will not...

32:46.921 --> 32:49.750
♪

32:53.972 --> 32:55.364
I survived.

32:55.538 --> 32:58.498
♪

32:58.585 --> 33:00.935
And this...

33:01.109 --> 33:04.286
♪

33:04.417 --> 33:07.028
I am supposed to be shattered
by this?

33:07.115 --> 33:10.118
♪

33:10.249 --> 33:11.902
Well, I won't be.

33:12.077 --> 33:14.993
♪

33:15.123 --> 33:17.125
I won't...
[ sobs ]

33:17.299 --> 33:20.085
♪

33:20.215 --> 33:22.130
[ sobs ]

33:22.304 --> 33:23.871
♪

33:23.958 --> 33:26.047
[ door opens ]

33:28.136 --> 33:29.790
- [ door closes ]
- Sorry.

33:31.052 --> 33:33.402
I didn't mean to wake you.

33:33.533 --> 33:35.317
How's Claire?

33:35.448 --> 33:39.104
Was she able to...

33:39.234 --> 33:40.844
Was she able to--
to talk about it?

33:42.933 --> 33:44.979
No.

33:45.110 --> 33:47.068
[ sighs ]

33:50.637 --> 33:52.378
It's still so raw.

33:55.511 --> 33:57.252
Though, to be honest,
I don't know if she ever will.

33:59.602 --> 34:01.430
[ sighs ]
Maybe she'll tell Da someday.

34:05.434 --> 34:08.220
What a horrific combination
of words for anyone to have
to find within themselves...

34:12.441 --> 34:14.530
And utter
to another being.

34:14.661 --> 34:17.490
[ somber music ]

34:17.577 --> 34:20.406
♪

34:22.321 --> 34:25.237
[ both sigh ]

34:25.324 --> 34:28.109
♪

34:39.120 --> 34:41.253
You haven't asked me
what happened.

34:44.299 --> 34:46.867
Did your father tell you?

34:47.041 --> 34:49.913
♪

34:50.044 --> 34:51.524
No.

34:51.698 --> 34:54.483
♪

34:57.095 --> 35:00.054
Brianna...

35:00.141 --> 35:01.099
I...

35:01.186 --> 35:04.145
Hey.

35:04.276 --> 35:05.364
What's wrong?

35:05.538 --> 35:08.454
♪

35:08.584 --> 35:11.065
Will ye hear me?

35:11.196 --> 35:13.067
[ exhales deeply ]

35:13.198 --> 35:14.634
You know I will.

35:14.721 --> 35:16.114
♪

35:16.201 --> 35:18.681
What is it?

35:18.812 --> 35:20.640
Listen to what I must tell you,

35:20.770 --> 35:22.424
and then please, God,
tell me I have done right.

35:22.598 --> 35:25.558
♪

35:25.688 --> 35:27.386
You don't have
to tell me anything.

35:27.516 --> 35:29.518
I do.

35:29.692 --> 35:32.695
♪

35:32.826 --> 35:35.089
Will you put out the candle?

35:35.263 --> 35:38.136
♪

35:44.881 --> 35:46.405
I-I killed a man.

35:46.579 --> 35:49.495
♪

35:49.625 --> 35:51.323
[ birds chirping ]

35:54.282 --> 35:57.067
[ uneasy music ]

35:57.242 --> 35:59.722
♪

35:59.809 --> 36:02.595
[ Lionel wheezes ]

36:02.682 --> 36:05.511
♪

36:08.818 --> 36:11.604
[ Lionel groans ]

36:14.346 --> 36:16.870
- Have mercy on me.
- Be quiet.

36:16.957 --> 36:19.525
What do you think this is,
if not mercy?

36:19.655 --> 36:21.222
LIONEL:
Can you at least
loosen my bonds?

36:21.353 --> 36:22.615
MARSALI:
Quiet.

36:22.702 --> 36:25.531
♪

36:29.230 --> 36:31.058
Don't let him kill me...

36:31.189 --> 36:33.147
that husband of yours.

36:33.321 --> 36:35.584
♪

36:35.671 --> 36:39.109
Marsali...

36:39.240 --> 36:41.242
can you steep the comfrey...

36:41.373 --> 36:43.418
- and prepare the syringe?
- Aye.

36:43.549 --> 36:46.682
[ wheezes ]

36:46.769 --> 36:48.684
MARSALI:
Wasting good medicine
on the likes of you.

36:48.771 --> 36:51.687
♪

36:51.818 --> 36:55.430
[ groaning ]

36:55.561 --> 36:59.129
I implore you,
Mistress Fraser.

36:59.217 --> 37:00.609
Please...

37:00.783 --> 37:03.569
♪

37:21.500 --> 37:24.024
[ Lionel wheezes ]

37:24.198 --> 37:27.114
♪

37:27.245 --> 37:28.985
I will do you no harm.

37:29.159 --> 37:31.945
♪

37:45.350 --> 37:48.178
[ cries ]

37:50.180 --> 37:52.966
[ sobbing ]

38:19.471 --> 38:21.386
What about a little bit
of mercy

38:21.516 --> 38:22.996
on my poor old appetite?

38:23.083 --> 38:25.781
Ye'll take what ye get,
when ye get it.

38:25.912 --> 38:28.393
I always do.

38:28.480 --> 38:30.525
[ chuckles ]

38:30.656 --> 38:32.353
You might want
to watch your words.

38:32.484 --> 38:35.313
I hardly think I need to worry
about that, now, do I?

38:36.923 --> 38:38.533
Damn women.

38:38.664 --> 38:40.622
I prefer my supper
with a smile,

38:40.753 --> 38:42.015
thank you very much.

38:42.145 --> 38:43.538
So, when you're good
and ready...

38:43.669 --> 38:46.019
[ wheezes ]

38:48.761 --> 38:51.329
[ sighs ]

38:51.459 --> 38:53.243
And, you know...

38:53.374 --> 38:56.856
if I'm not well treated,

38:56.986 --> 38:59.946
my brother--he will come
with his men,

39:00.076 --> 39:02.470
and he will slaughter you

39:02.601 --> 39:05.517
and burn the houses
over your heads
while you sleep.

39:07.780 --> 39:10.043
Well...

39:10.173 --> 39:13.829
we must make sure
you return home
hale and strong.

39:13.916 --> 39:15.353
[ grunts ]

39:17.790 --> 39:18.791
What's that for?

39:20.967 --> 39:23.796
I've been learning
the art of healing.

39:23.926 --> 39:26.102
Mistress Fraser
has taught me well.

39:27.452 --> 39:29.323
[ grunts ]

39:29.454 --> 39:30.933
She took an oath

39:31.020 --> 39:33.501
to do no harm.

39:33.632 --> 39:35.198
[ grunts ]

39:35.329 --> 39:36.330
I have taken no such oath.

39:36.504 --> 39:38.506
♪

39:38.637 --> 39:41.422
You hurt me.
You hurt my family.

39:41.553 --> 39:43.859
You hurt my ma.

39:43.946 --> 39:46.645
I'll watch you burn in hell

39:46.775 --> 39:48.647
before I let you harm
another soul in this house.

39:48.777 --> 39:50.823
[ grunts ]

39:50.953 --> 39:53.608
[ suspenseful music ]

39:58.918 --> 40:01.703
[ dramatic music ]

40:01.877 --> 40:04.663
♪

40:09.711 --> 40:13.019
[ footsteps approaching ]

40:13.149 --> 40:14.324
JAMIE: Marsali?

40:18.024 --> 40:20.809
♪

40:24.509 --> 40:26.032
[ grunts softly ]

40:26.162 --> 40:29.383
He thought me no better
than the dirt under his boot.

40:29.557 --> 40:32.560
♪

40:32.691 --> 40:34.388
A mere woman
of no consequence.

40:34.562 --> 40:37.522
♪

40:37.652 --> 40:39.785
What's done is done.

40:39.872 --> 40:43.310
Will this...

40:43.397 --> 40:46.574
Will-will he--
is he...

40:46.705 --> 40:48.663
Will he haunt me?

40:48.794 --> 40:50.622
Shh, shh, shh.

40:50.752 --> 40:52.711
Mm, am I going to hell?

40:52.841 --> 40:54.364
[ cries ]

40:54.452 --> 40:57.367
Nothing to fear, lass.

40:57.498 --> 40:58.586
Here.

40:58.760 --> 41:01.502
♪

41:26.092 --> 41:28.790
[ indistinct chatter ]

41:28.877 --> 41:31.706
♪

41:49.115 --> 41:50.682
Fraser's here.

41:50.769 --> 41:53.380
♪

42:08.047 --> 42:10.528
[ breathing heavily ]

42:11.920 --> 42:13.705
Fraser?

42:15.097 --> 42:17.578
A band of men
came upon my land.

42:17.709 --> 42:20.668
They abducted
and violated my wife.

42:20.799 --> 42:23.366
I followed them...

42:23.453 --> 42:26.108
killed them all.

42:26.239 --> 42:28.894
I brought you your brother...

42:29.024 --> 42:30.983
so you may bury him.

42:36.684 --> 42:37.990
I thank you for that.

42:40.688 --> 42:42.429
Lionel...

42:45.040 --> 42:47.303
He reaped what he sowed.

42:50.045 --> 42:51.743
And you did what you must.

43:02.536 --> 43:04.582
As will I...

43:04.712 --> 43:06.714
[ ominous music ]

43:06.845 --> 43:08.890
When the time comes.

43:09.064 --> 43:11.850
♪

43:25.994 --> 43:27.822
JAMIE:
I have lived through war

43:27.953 --> 43:30.999
and lost much.

43:31.130 --> 43:34.960
I know what's worth a fight
and what is not.

43:35.090 --> 43:39.051
Honor and courage
are matters of the bone.

43:39.181 --> 43:42.707
And what a man will kill for,
he'll sometimes die for, too.

43:42.837 --> 43:44.578
[ indistinct chatter ]

43:44.752 --> 43:47.668
♪

43:47.799 --> 43:50.802
A man's life springs
from his woman's bones,

43:50.932 --> 43:53.892
and in her blood
is his honor christened.

43:54.022 --> 43:56.285
For the sake of love alone

43:56.416 --> 43:58.679
will I walk
through fire again.

43:58.766 --> 44:01.377
[ dog barks ]

44:01.508 --> 44:05.251
ROGER:
There was a time
not so long ago

44:05.381 --> 44:08.776
that I wasn't sure
we'd ever be walking up
to this house again.

44:08.907 --> 44:11.866
But here we are.

44:11.997 --> 44:15.217
We always seem to be
on the road less traveled.

44:15.348 --> 44:17.916
Nothing is ever easy.

44:18.003 --> 44:20.092
"I shall be telling this
with a sigh

44:20.222 --> 44:22.050
"somewhere ages
and ages hence.

44:22.181 --> 44:25.227
"Two roads diverged
in a wood, and I?

44:25.358 --> 44:27.577
"I took the one
less traveled by,

44:27.708 --> 44:29.971
and that has made
all the difference."

44:30.102 --> 44:31.712
[ indistinct chatter,
dog barking ]

44:31.843 --> 44:34.410
- Show-off.
- [ chuckles ]

44:34.497 --> 44:36.674
We certainly have tried
to take a few different roads.

44:39.372 --> 44:41.026
Are you disappointed?

44:41.113 --> 44:43.593
No.

44:43.724 --> 44:45.987
We wanted the stones
to take us home,

44:46.118 --> 44:47.859
and they did.

44:52.080 --> 44:53.865
[ man chuckles ]

44:58.347 --> 45:00.872
[ footsteps ascending stairs ]

45:01.002 --> 45:03.875
[ indistinct chatter ]

45:04.005 --> 45:05.746
That post is crooked.

45:09.271 --> 45:11.926
Is that all?

45:12.057 --> 45:13.928
- I'll mend it now.
- No.

45:15.887 --> 45:17.540
We'll wait until tomorrow.

45:19.804 --> 45:23.024
Let's just enjoy this...

45:23.155 --> 45:24.591
ordinary day.

45:29.117 --> 45:33.208
Oh, who knows how much longer
we'll have this peace,

45:33.295 --> 45:34.993
knowing what's coming?

45:36.864 --> 45:37.778
Aye.

45:39.737 --> 45:41.564
Aye, the Revolution.

45:45.917 --> 45:49.659
The bravest are surely those
with the clearest vision

45:49.747 --> 45:52.140
of what is before them--

45:52.271 --> 45:56.101
glory, danger alike--

45:56.231 --> 45:58.886
yet notwithstanding,

45:59.017 --> 46:01.715
go out to meet it.

46:01.846 --> 46:05.066
That was Thucydides
who said that, not me.

46:05.197 --> 46:07.503
[ thunder rumbling ]

46:07.634 --> 46:10.506
Well, you'd know
all about that,
wouldn't you?

46:10.637 --> 46:13.640
Ah, it's only brave
when there's a choice
ye must make.

46:13.771 --> 46:15.729
[ tender music ]

46:15.860 --> 46:18.036
Well, we'll meet it
the best we can.

46:18.166 --> 46:19.907
[ thunder rumbling ]

46:20.081 --> 46:22.867
♪

46:27.828 --> 46:29.090
I love you.

46:29.177 --> 46:31.963
♪

46:39.057 --> 46:41.537
When the day shall come
that we do part...

46:43.322 --> 46:47.239
If my last words
are not "I love you,"

46:47.326 --> 46:51.199
ye ken it's because
I didna have time.

46:51.373 --> 46:54.159
♪

46:56.117 --> 46:58.903
[ thunder rumbles ]

46:59.077 --> 47:01.819
♪

